          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cr (weight=21.6 g) and Ta (weight=49 g) targets in the",
                "natural isotopic composition placed in cylinders of  2",
                "cm diameter and 2 cm high coaxial with the beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "P"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLATE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " ILFORD C2 emulsion, 200 mu thick, 1*3 square",
                "inches. A foil of lead 6 mm thick screened the plates",
                "against the low energy photons coming from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrected for:",
                " a) the useful solid angle of the recoil tracks in the",
                "    center of mass system,",
                " b) the probability of escape of the tracks from the",
                "    emulsion,",
                " c) the cross section for n-p collisions in the",
                "    emulsion,",
                " d) the number of hydrogen atoms per unit volume of",
                "    nuclear emulsion,",
                " e) the gamma-ray absorption in the target,",
                " f) the neutron absorption in the target and in the",
                "    lead screen.",
                "The background was negligible."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "4PI1A"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors are presented."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "THEO",
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  The authors try to fit the high energy",
                "tails of the spectra in the frame of the Wilkinson",
                "photoeffect model with some particularization of the",
                "shells from which high energy neutrons are supposed",
                "to came.  The energy distributions of neutrons in the",
                "low energy range are compared with the evaporation",
                "theory. The calculated yields derived by spectra are",
                "compared with the experimental yields of high energy",
                "neutrons obtained by Ferrero and co-authors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The high  energy tail of the photoneutrons, coming",
                "from some direct process, shows, also in Cr and Ta,",
                "the small maxima at 5-6 MeV neutron energy. The tail",
                "accounts for 10% of all the photoneutrons observed.",
                "The increase in the yield of the high energy tails",
                "from 20 to 30 MeV in Cr and Ta is consistent with the",
                "second maximum in the cross section found by Ferrero",
                "and co-authors."
              ]
            }
          ],
